<h2>Frequently Asked Questions — LG Dryer Repair Studio City</h2>

<h3>How much does LG dryer repair cost in Studio City?</h3>
<p>Same pricing as LA County — no Studio City surcharge. Most repairs $280–380. Most common Studio City call — thermal fuse plus vent cleaning — $430–550 combined, done same visit. The $65 diagnostic fee is waived when you approve the repair.</p>

<h3>My LG dryer runs but won't heat in Studio City — what's wrong?</h3>
<p>Two most likely causes depending on your model. DLGX gas or electric: thermal fuse behind the lint filter — blown from vent restriction. DLEX electric front-load: thermal fuse on the blower housing, same cause. We test both the fuse and heating element with a multimeter before recommending either. Same symptom, different part, different price — you don't pay element prices if the fuse is the actual problem.</p>

<h3>My LG dryer ends cycles too early and clothes are still damp — what's wrong?</h3>
<p>Almost certainly the moisture sensor bar coated with fabric softener residue — the sensor reads false "dry" signals and ends cycles early. We test sensor function on every Studio City "runs but doesn't dry" call. Cleaning on-site is free. Sensor replacement $150–200 if the bar itself has failed.</p>

<h3>Can you come before my call time at CBS Studio Center?</h3>
<p>Yes — morning slots available. Call (323) 990-7550 and tell us your call time. We'll confirm whether we can be there before. Monday through Saturday 8am–7pm, Sunday 9am–5pm.</p>

<h3>My LG dryer in my Studio City hillside home shows d80 — what does that mean?</h3>
<p>80% airflow restriction. Hillside homes above Mulholland have unconventional vent routing — exits through hillside walls, downward sections, caps in landscaping. We assess the full vent path. Cleaning alone may not fix it if the routing is causing the restriction.</p>

<h3>Do you offer same-day LG dryer repair in Studio City?</h3>
<p>Yes — typically 1–2 hours from your call. Call (323) 990-7550, Monday through Saturday 8am–7pm, Sunday 9am–5pm.</p>

<h3>Why won't my LG dryer start in Studio City even though the door looks closed?</h3>
<p>On DLGX4001 and DLEX3001 models especially, the door can look and feel shut while the safety switch inside the latch isn't fully engaging — and the dryer won't start until it confirms the door is latched. Our LG Dryer Repair techs test the door switch with a multimeter first; a latch replacement is $150–180 and about 30–40 minutes, with the $65 diagnostic waived when you approve the repair. We're licensed with the Bureau of Household Goods and Services (#49573).</p>

<h3>Is it worth repairing an LG dryer in Studio City, or replacing it?</h3>
<p>For most single-component failures, yes — repairs run $280–380 versus $800–1,500 for a new LG dryer, and many Studio City no-heat calls are a $280–350 thermal fuse plus vent cleaning rather than a dead machine. We give you an honest read on-site if an older machine has multiple issues.</p>

